column5: Entrez Gene identifier equivalences. Gene and Gene Product namespace equivalences are rooted to Entrez Gene, such that each Entrez Gene identifier is assigned a unique UUID.
column6: HGNC symbol equivalences based on the Entrez Gene gene_info file. HGNC Symbols without an associated Entrez GeneID are assigned a new UUID.
column7: MGI symbol equivalences based on the Entrez Gene gene_info file. MGI Symbols without an associated Entrez GeneID are assigned a new UUID.
column8: RGD symbol equivalences based on the Entrez Gene gene_info file. RGD Symbols without an associated Entrez GeneID are assigned a new UUID.
column9: Swiss-Prot entry name equivalences to Entrez Gene are assigned based on the database cross references provided by UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot. Entry names that map to no Gene IDs or more than one Gene ID are assigned a new UUID.
column10: Swiss-Prot accession number equivalences are assigned based on the correpsonding Swiss-Prot entry name.
column11: Affymetrix probe set identifier equivalences were derived from mappings to Entrez Gene IDs from NetAffx. For probe sets annotated to multiple Entrez Gene IDs, a single ID was selected as follows: the Entrez Gene ID with the highest priority RefSeq status was selected (from high to low priority - Reviewed, Validated, Provisional, Predicted, Model, Inferred, none). Gene IDs with the RefSeq status 'suppressed' were not used. When multiple Entrez Gene IDs shared the highest priority RefSeq status, the lowest numbered ID was selected.
column12: MeSH Disease Headings equivalences were obtained from the Disease Ontology cross-references to MeSH.
column13: MeSH Phenomena and Processes equivalences were obtained by string match to GO Biological Process names.
column14: Disease Ontology Name equivalences. Disease namespace equivalences are rooted to Disease Ontology names, such that each Disease Ontology name is assigned a unique UUID.
column15: Selventa Legacy Disease Name equivalences were assigned based on string match to Disease Ontology names.
column16: GO Biological Process Name equivalences are assigned based on the correpsonding GO Biological Process identifier.
column17: GO Biological Process Identifier equivalences. Biological Process namespace equivalences are rooted to GO, such that each primary GO Biological Process identifier is assigned a unique UUID.
column18: ChEBI Identifier equivalences. Chemical and small molecule namespace equivalences are rooted to ChEBI, such that each primary ChEBI identifier is assigned a unique UUID.
column19: ChEBI Name equivalences are assigned based on the correpsonding ChEBI identifier.
column20: PubChem Compound ID equivalences to ChEBI IDs are assigned based on the PubChem SID-Map file. Compound IDs without an equivalent ChEBI ID are assigned a new UUID.
column21: Selventa Legacy Chemical equivalences were assigned based on string match to ChEBI synonyms.
column23: GO Cellular Component Identifier equivalences. Cell component and complex namespace equivalences are rooted to GO, such that each primary GO identifier is assigned a unique UUID.
column24: GO Cellular Component Name equivalences are assigned based on the correpsonding GO Cellular Component identifier.
column25: Selventa Named Complex equivalences were assigned based on manual mapping to GO Cellular Components
column26: Selventa Named Complex equivalences were assigned based on manual mapping to GO Cellular Components
